UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. George Steven TRABER, Defendant-Appellant. Nos. 71-1462-71-1939

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Sept. 1, 1971. Milton E. Grusmark, Miami Beach, Fla., for defendant-appellant. Robert W. Rust, U. S. Atty., Miami, Fla., Richard A. Hauser, Asst. U. S. Atty., Miami, Fla., for plaintiff-appel-lee.

Before BELL, AINSWORTH and GODBOLD, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir.; See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5 Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1
